&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The job in short&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join the banking revolution! As the global leader in Engagement Banking, Backbase is at the forefront of revolutionizing banking services through technology. We are looking for a skilled Platform Engineer to join our Wealth Team, where we build the next generation of digital investment solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be the backbone of our software delivery, ensuring that our Investment applications are deployed and managed under the highest professional standards of Cloud Ops. You will bridge the gap between software development and operations, focusing on Resilience, Availability, and Scalability to provide a seamless experience for our banking customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet the job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;●Ensure the availability and reliability of the managed hosting service we provide to our customers;&lt;br&gt;●Ensure that the solution always runs in a compliant, secure and cost-effective way;&lt;br&gt;●Participate in our on-call pool and help to ensure maximum reliability, high availability and uptime;&lt;br&gt;●Help foster a culture of continuous learning and improvement;&lt;br&gt;●Troubleshoot and resolve infrastructure-related issues, ensuring resilience, availability and scalability within Wealth Domain;&lt;br&gt;●Contribute to increasing operational efficiency and helping to bring overall cloud cost under control.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How about you?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proficient with tools and tech like Helm Charts, Kubernetes, Istio, ArgoCD, Github/GHA;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Monitoring and Observability, particularly the Grafana stack and OpenTelemetry (OTEL), is desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an understanding of cloud infrastructure security, cloud-native technologies, and desired state configuration;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have strong communication skills allowing you to drive initiatives and decisions inside and outside your team;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have at least 5 years of experience in system engineering including at least 3 years of working with the aforementioned technologies;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You combine technical excellence with mentorship skills, and provide your peers with hands-on guidance and collaborative problem-solving;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are focused on automation-first. Not content with anything manual, your goal is to make every process predictable and automated;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have knowledge of designing and implementing scalable, highly-available cloud infrastructure;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Python stack is a plus;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have good English communication skills to collaborate with international teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Backbase has entered a new era of digital banking with the launch of the world’s first &lt;strong&gt;AI-Native Banking OS&lt;/strong&gt;. This is not just a platform; it is a fundamental shift in how banks operate. By unifying digital channels, front-office workspaces, and back-office operations under a single &lt;strong&gt;Control Plane&lt;/strong&gt;, we enable banks to run as one. Our OS coordinates execution across customers, employees, and AI agents, ensuring every action is authorized, governed, and context-aware. At Backbase, we are transforming the promise of AI into measurable business impact for over 120 leading financial institutions globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Principal AI Engineer - &lt;strong&gt;Banking OS Control Plane for Integrations&lt;/strong&gt; is a pivotal role within our Ecosystems department. In this role, you won&#39;t just be using tools to build connectors; you will be the core engineer responsible for building and enhancing the Integrations Control Plane - &lt;strong&gt;Connector Studio&lt;/strong&gt;—our proprietary, AI-powered platform designed to enable the seamless creation of connectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will architect the intelligent engine and the platform tools that empower teams to integrate diverse banking systems effortlessly. You are building the &quot;brain&quot; and the machinery of the Connectivity and Integration Layer (powered by Grand Central), which acts as the critical bridge between our intelligent frontline and the complex world of legacy core systems, CRMs, and fintechs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Principal AI Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; with a passion and deep knowledge in building intelligent, context-aware agentic systems, tools, and platforms. You’ll play a key role in leading the development of the AI-powered studio, creating the intelligent workflows and automated tools that simplify and accelerate the generation of complex banking connectors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🚀 &lt;strong&gt;Experienced&lt;/strong&gt;: Minimum 8 years in software engineering, with 5+ years developing and delivering enterprise-grade AI applications.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🧠 &lt;strong&gt;Technically Strong&lt;/strong&gt;: Expert proficiency in Python, Django, and hands-on mastery of Agentic AI frameworks (LangGraph, LangChain, Agno), RAG architectures, and API-first design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🧩 &lt;strong&gt;Agentic Thinker&lt;/strong&gt;: Well-versed in modern AI agent patterns including &lt;strong&gt;MCP&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;A2A&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;ACP&lt;/strong&gt;. You understand how to build modular systems where agents collaborate, reason, and adapt to context dynamically.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🛠️ &lt;strong&gt;MLOps / LLMOps Savvy&lt;/strong&gt;: You’re comfortable with model lifecycle management, prompt versioning, fine tuning, context management, agent monitoring, and AI experimentation using platforms like Azure AI Foundry, HuggingFace, and LangChain.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;☁️ &lt;strong&gt;Cloud &amp;amp; Infra Native&lt;/strong&gt;: Good knowledge of cloud platforms (preferably Azure), Kubernetes for AI workloads, and CI/CD pipelines that support rapid and reliable delivery.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🌟 &lt;strong&gt;Startup Mindset&lt;/strong&gt;: You&#39;re a self-starter—proactive, resourceful, curious, and comfortable moving fast.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🗣️ &lt;strong&gt;Excellent Collaborator and Mentor&lt;/strong&gt;: A strong communicator who leads by example—champions clear documentation, promotes knowledge sharing, and enjoys mentoring others to elevate team capabilities and drive scalable impact..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engineering Team Lead (ETL)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Job in Short&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ETL is the &quot;Captain&quot; of a single squad. This is a &quot;player-coach&quot; role focused on delivery&amp;nbsp;predictability, people leadership, and day-to-day execution. You are a Senior+ Engineer who&amp;nbsp;manages people, not a manager who used to code; if you cannot open the IDE and debug a&amp;nbsp;production issue, you cannot perform this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meet the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery Mastery: Optimize the team’s &quot;Idea to Production&quot; cycle time and&amp;nbsp;strengthen delivery predictability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Talent Density: Own 1:1s, performance calibration, hiring decisions, and succession&amp;nbsp;planning for your squad of 6–9 engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on Leadership: Spend ~50% of your time on system design and ~20% on&amp;nbsp;hands-on development like code reviews and unblocking technical issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conflict Resolution: Mediate interpersonal or cross-team conflicts early to protect team&amp;nbsp;cohesion and delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS Detector: Use your technical depth to spot unrealistic estimates, fragile designs,&amp;nbsp;or risk blind spots.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Response: During critical incidents, jump in technically or coordinate the&amp;nbsp;response effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI-Native Engineering: Lead the adoption of agentic tooling, LLM workflows, and AI&amp;nbsp;automation within your team to accelerate the development lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How About You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 5+ years of experience and have shipped production code recently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have an explicit desire to lead people but remain an active technical contributor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You possess high emotional intelligence and resilience under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a strong&amp;nbsp;unblocker who translates and synthesizes rather than just relaying messages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are an &lt;strong&gt;experienced&lt;/strong&gt; Engineer who manages people, not a manager who used to code.. If you cannot open an IDE, spin up an agentic coding session in Cursor or Claude Code, debug a production issue or support a customer implementation alongside our last-mile Services teams, this is not the right role. You are the captain of a single squad: accountable for delivery predictability, engineering quality and the growth of every engineer in your team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for technologists who want to stay deep in the technology whilst taking on genuine people leadership and delivery accountability. You will spend roughly half your time on system design, architecture and technical decision-making, with around a fifth of your time in the codebase directly through code reviews, debugging and unblocking. The remaining time is invested in your people: coaching, calibration, hiring and building a team that delivers predictably and sustainably.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hands-on Leadership: Spend ~70% of your time on development activities like code reviews , design work, and unblocking technical issues&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;System Design and Architecture:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Lead and participate in design reviews, RFCs and architecture decisions alongside Staff Engineers. Ensure security and scalability are embedded from the start.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-on Contribution:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Maintain your technical credibility through active code reviews, debugging production issues and unblocking your team. You write code, read code and understand the systems your squad owns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Quality and Engineering Excellence:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Champion modern engineering practices including CI/CD pipelines, test automation, observability and quality gates. Drive production-readiness and robust release management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emergency Response:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;During critical incidents, jump in technically or coordinate the response. You are comfortable leading under pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-Native Engineering:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Lead adoption of agentic tooling, LLM workflows and AI automation within your squad to accelerate the development lifecycle. Experiment with code generation, test automation and AI-assisted productivity tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;People Leadership (circa 10% of the role)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Talent Development:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Own meaningful 1:1s, performance calibration, and evidence-based career development for your squad of 6 to 9 engineers. Create tailored growth plans and act as a genuine coach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Health:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Build and sustain psychological safety, team resilience and a healthy engineering culture. Detect and resolve friction early. Maintain sustainable pace even under delivery pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
